    <h1>1&#xD;&#xA;AD&#xAD;VEN&#xAD;TURE OF THE RING</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201126/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-11-26"><time>2020-11-26</time></a>
        - <span>TELEVISION</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>Pre­mieres at 9pm on Dec 13 on HBO (StarHub TV Chan­nel 601 and Sing­tel TV Chan­nel 420) and HBO Go</p>
    <p>This orig­i­nal ro­man­tic-com­edy se­ries from HBO Asia tells the sto­ries of cou­ples who come into con­tact with a mis­placed en­gage­ment ring.</p>
    <p>It stars Tai­wanese ac­tor Chris Wang (The Shrewd Wife, 2010), who plays Yi-zhi, an ac­tu­ary and base­ball fan, and Tai­wanese ac­tress Al­li­son Lin (Love By De­sign, 2016) as his free-spir­ited flight at­ten­dant girl­friend Lisa.</p>
    <p>The story kicks off when Yi-zhi’s metic­u­lously planned pro­posal goes awry – he loses the en­gage­ment ring on a train.</p>

